<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="434" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source"><persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador to the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HWA2" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Presidents
                                Special Assistant</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HHL1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d434fn1">Sent to Cairo via Army channels.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-04">December 4, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Through Russian Embassy Teheran message from <persName corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> “Vishin-sky will represent USSR at Cairo”.<note n="2" xml:id="d434fn2"><persName corresp="#p_VSA1">Vinogradov</persName>, not <persName corresp="#p_VAY1">Vyshinsky</persName>, represented the Soviet Union at Cairo
                                during the Second Cairo Conference, but he attended none of the
                                formal meetings. See <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_839">pp. 839</ref>, <ref target="#pg_858">858</ref>.</note> I will leave Teheran for Moscow morning fifth
                            current month.</p>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>